approach: 

1. priority queue approach.
2. using sorting.

approach 1:
(kth minimum)
1.insert elements into priority queue(by default they are in descending order)
2.until k=0, pop out elements from priority queue.
3. return top element.

(kth maximum)
1. insert elements into priority queue(change declaration:priority_queue<int,vector<int>,greater<int>>p)
2.until k=0, pop out elements from priority queue.
3. return top element.
